Japan Budget Requests Reach Record 99 Trillion Yen, Nikkei Says

-- B y   Y u s u k e   M i y a z a w a
-- 
2011-10-01T01:21:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-01/japan-budget-requests-reach-record-99-trillion-yen-nikkei-says.html
Japanese ministries submitted a
record 99 trillion yen ($1.3 trillion) in budget requests for
the fiscal year starting April 2012, including funding for
earthquake recovery, safeguarding of nuclear power plants and
stimulating economic growth, the Nikkei newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yusuke Miyazawa in Tokyo at 
